The East African country goes to the polls on October 28 to elect a President, members of parliament and councillors. This will be the country's fifth general election since the reintroduction of the multiparty system in the country in 1992 while President John Magufuli has pledged a peaceful and credible process, the election comes amid concerns of narrowing freedoms and increasing authoritarianism. For more on what to expect Channel Africa spoke to Bubelwa Kaiza, a Tanzanian Political Commentator...
